{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3191d0d9-5190-4b80-908c-09778df7afc3","content":"Yes, both properties are correct for .NET MAUI (including .NET 10). Here's a quick summary:\n\n**`ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"`** — Correct. Add it to your `ContentPage` to keep content out of the notch/home indicator areas. You'll need the iOS platform-specific namespace:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage\n    xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n    ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\">\n```\n\n**`IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"`** — Also correct. Apply it to individual views (like an `Image` or `Grid`) that should extend *behind* the notch/rounded corners (e.g., a full-bleed background image):\n\n```xml\n<Grid IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\">\n    <Image Source=\"background.png\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n</Grid>\n```\n\n**Typical pattern:** Use both together — `UseSafeArea` on the page to protect text/buttons, then `IgnoreSafeArea` on a specific background element so it fills edge-to-edge.\n\nThese APIs have been stable since early MAUI releases and remain the recommended approach in .NET 10.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"329bf694-7218-4e9f-8ed6-e3b2a4da09dc","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI safe area handling on iOS, specifically about two properties:\n\n1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` - a platform-specific property for ContentPage\n2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` - on a Grid for background images\n\nLet me search for information about these APIs in the current repository context, and also use my knowledge about .NET MAUI.\n\nFrom my knowledge:\n\n1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` - This is a valid iOS platform-specific property in .NET MAUI. It's used on ContentPage to ensure content respects the safe area (notch, home indicator, etc.).\n\n\n2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` - This is also a valid property in .NET MAUI that can be set on views to allow them to extend beyond the safe area. I should verify if there were any changes in .NET 9 or 10 regarding safe area handling, as there have been some updates to how MAUI manages safe areas across different versions.\n\nLooking at what I know, `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` has been the standard approach since Xamarin.Forms and should still be valid in .NET MAUI, and `IgnoreSafeArea` on individual views is also a supported property. Without specific knowledge of breaking changes in .NET 10, these APIs should continue to work as expected. Both approaches are valid for handling safe areas in .NET MAUI, so I'll confirm these are the correct solutions.","outputTokens":1072,"requestId":"B7D0:2A1B2F:1ABBD5:22B777:69FFDB8B"},"id":"81a02cee-23fa-48af-9f0a-f3eece61360c","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:13:06.810Z","parentId":"53b1a4cb-f458-4578-a611-9ad9fb6a7a6d"}
